prayers.text:
He is God
O Thou kind, bounteous, merciful Lord,
illumine this gathering with the lamp of Thy love, and quicken these souls with the breaths of the Holy Spirit;
bestow heavenly lights, grant the great gift, send divine confirmations, and vouchsafe spiritual revelations;
illume the eyes with the light of guidance, and make the hearts rejoice with infinite blessings;
give the spirits the great tidings, and honour the souls with the supreme gift.
O Lord, we are poor, grant us the treasure of Thy kingdom;
we are humbled, make us honoured in Thy kingdom;
we are without shelter, grant us refuge and abode in Thy protection;
we are seekers, guide us with Thy endless graces;
we are silent, grant us eloquent speech;
we are without strength, bestow upon us the power of Thy kingdom.
O Lord, O Forgiver, forgive our faults, bestow grace, pardon our sins;
teach us the ways of Thy mercy.
Thou art the Giver, Thou art the Forgiver, Thou art the Merciful.

He is God

O Beloved of these lovers, and the Object of desire of these seekers,
grant unto us, who are distressed, tranquility of heart;
make us, who are needy, rich;
grant unto us, who are ailing, a remedy;
and unto us, who are wounded and suffering, bestow a balm.
Guide us, who are lost;
quench our thirst;
grant rest and peace unto us, who are in turmoil;
bestow upon us, who are abased, the radiance of glory;
stretch forth Thy hand unto us, who have fallen;
grant unto us, who are grieved, joy;
and bestow upon us, who are dejected, warmth and ardour.
Make us successful in the service of Thy friends, and aid us in the adoration of Thy companions.
This is the utmost desire of heart and soul;
this is the utmost hope of all worlds and consciousness.
